WEBVTT

00:00.041 --> 00:01.917
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i>
<i>"RED BAND SOCIETY"...</i>

00:01.917 --> 00:03.166
Charlie:<i> I'M IN A COMA.</i>

00:03.166 --> 00:06.291
<i>YEAH. THIS IS ME TALKING TO YOU</i>
<i>FROM A COMA.</i>

00:06.291 --> 00:08.542
THIS PLACE IS CRAWLING
WITH MEDICAL MARIJUANA.

00:08.542 --> 00:10.250
-SERIOUSLY?
-BUZZKILL.

00:10.250 --> 00:12.583
-WHY ARE YOU HERE?
-I HAVE CANCER...IN MY LEG.

00:12.583 --> 00:13.709
YOU'RE GONNA GET
THROUGH IT.

00:13.709 --> 00:14.709
IT'S EASY FOR YOU
TO SAY.

00:14.709 --> 00:16.917
NOT REALLY.

00:16.917 --> 00:18.667
I DON'T SMOKE, DRINK,
OR DO DRUGS.

00:18.667 --> 00:20.208
SO UNHEALTHY, RIGHT?

00:20.208 --> 00:22.000
NOT LIKE
STARVING YOURSELF.

00:22.000 --> 00:22.959
Jackson:
WE DRUG-TESTED HER.

00:22.959 --> 00:24.959
WE FOUND COCAINE, MARIJUANA.

00:24.959 --> 00:25.917
AND THAT
IS GOING TO PUT HER

00:25.917 --> 00:27.834
AT THE BOTTOM OF
THE WAITING LIST FOR A HEART.

00:27.834 --> 00:29.375
Leo: I'VE BEEN WEARING THESE
FOR A LONG TIME.

00:29.375 --> 00:30.750
IT'S TIME TO LET THEM GO.

00:30.750 --> 00:32.166
THIS IS FROM MY FIRST TRIP
TO THE E.R.

00:32.166 --> 00:33.375
EMMA...

00:33.375 --> 00:35.208
THIS IS
FROM MY FIRST SURGERY.

00:35.208 --> 00:36.583
-THANKS, LEO.
-JORDI...

00:36.583 --> 00:38.500
AND I WANT YOU TO KNOW
YOU'RE NOT ALONE.

00:38.500 --> 00:40.041
MY RED BAND. IT MUST HAVE
FALLEN OFF SOMEWHERE.

00:40.041 --> 00:42.500
I'LL FIND YOU
ANOTHER ONE.

00:51.458 --> 00:53.291
[ QUEEN'S "HAMMER TO FALL"
PLAYS ]

00:58.792 --> 01:00.250
♪ YEAH! ♪

01:04.500 --> 01:06.417
<i>THEY SAY TO REALLY UNDERSTAND</i>
<i>SOMEONE,</i>

01:06.417 --> 01:08.583
<i>YOU HAVE TO WALK A MILE</i>
<i>IN THEIR SHOES.</i>

01:08.583 --> 01:11.208
<i>BUT SOME SHOES ARE HARDER</i>
<i>TO WALK IN THAN OTHERS,</i>

01:11.208 --> 01:14.917
<i>MAYBE BECAUSE SOME PEOPLE</i>
<i>DON'T WANT TO LET YOU IN.</i>

01:14.917 --> 01:16.875
♪ MAKE THE BED ♪

01:16.875 --> 01:19.375
<i>AND SOME PEOPLE, ESPECIALLY</i>
<i>THOSE OF THE ONE-SHOE VARIETY,</i>

01:19.375 --> 01:21.041
<i>WOULDN'T KNOW</i>
HOW<i> TO LET YOU IN,</i>

01:21.041 --> 01:22.750
<i>EVEN IF THEY DID WANT TO.</i>

01:22.750 --> 01:26.208
♪ YOU DON'T WASTE
NO TIME AT ALL ♪

01:26.208 --> 01:29.542
♪ DON'T HEAR THE BELL
BUT YOU ANSWER THE CALL ♪

01:29.542 --> 01:32.583
<i>THE SHOE METAPHOR BASICALLY</i>
<i>BOILS DOWN TO EMPATHY,</i>

01:32.583 --> 01:36.041
<i>BUT IN ORDER TO APPRECIATE HOW</i>
<i>OTHER PEOPLE MIGHT BE FEELING,</i>

01:36.041 --> 01:38.917
<i>YOU HAVE TO BE ABLE TO</i>
<i>UNDERSTAND YOUR OWN FEELINGS.</i>

01:38.917 --> 01:40.834
<i>AND THAT GETS TRICKY,</i>

01:40.834 --> 01:42.792
<i>ESPECIALLY SINCE</i>
<i>MOST KIDS MY AGE</i>

01:42.792 --> 01:45.208
<i>WORK HARD TO PRETEND</i>
<i>THEY DON'T HAVE </i>ANY<i> FEELINGS.</i>

01:45.208 --> 01:49.125
<i>FEELINGS JUST AREN'T COOL,</i>
<i>UNLESS YOU'RE IN A COMA,</i>

01:49.125 --> 01:53.250
<i>LIKE ME, IN WHICH CASE,</i>
<i>FEELINGS ARE ALL YOU'VE GOT.</i>

01:53.250 --> 01:55.709
♪ JUST GOT TIME TO SAY
YOUR PRAYERS ♪

01:55.709 --> 02:03.000
♪ YEAH, WHILE YOU'RE WAITING
FOR THE HAMMER TO FALL ♪

02:11.458 --> 02:13.583
AND IT'S LEO ROTH
FOR THE WIN!

02:13.583 --> 02:15.125
THE CROWD GOES WILD!

02:15.125 --> 02:18.125
LADIES FLASH THEIR FUNBAGS
IN DEFERENCE! WHOO!

02:18.125 --> 02:20.542
YEAH, 'CAUSE THAT HAPPENS
IN GOLF.

02:20.542 --> 02:22.291
ARE YOU SURE THIS ISN'T GONNA
BREAK YOUR NEW LEG?

02:22.291 --> 02:25.333
UH, YEAH. WOULD THAT BE
SO TERRIBLE?

02:25.333 --> 02:27.208
YOUR PARENTS MIGHT THINK SO,

02:27.208 --> 02:28.834
SEEING AS THEY'RE THE ONES
WHO PAID FOR IT.

02:28.834 --> 02:30.291
ALSO,
YOUR PHYSICAL THERAPIST

02:30.291 --> 02:32.000
WILL PROBABLY HAVE AN OPINION
ON THE SUBJECT.

02:32.000 --> 02:32.917
-[ SIREN WAILING ]
-SPEAKING OF WHICH,

02:32.917 --> 02:34.959
AREN'T YOU MEANT TO BE WORKING
WITH HIM RIGHT NOW?

02:34.959 --> 02:36.875
WELL,
AREN'T YOU THE MOTHER HEN?

02:36.875 --> 02:38.333
NO WONDER YOU TWO BROKE UP.

02:38.333 --> 02:40.291
#RexyAin'tSexy.

02:40.291 --> 02:43.291
GUYS, DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT'S HAPPENING RIGHT NOW?

02:43.291 --> 02:44.375
CLIMATE CHANGE?

02:44.375 --> 02:45.709
NO PEACE
IN THE MIDDLE EAST?

02:45.709 --> 02:46.834
PREGNANT KARDASHIAN?

02:48.166 --> 02:50.333
JORDI'S ABOUT TO LOSE
HIS LEG.

02:50.333 --> 02:51.875
OH, YOU MEANT,
LIKE,<i> NOW </i>NOW.

02:51.875 --> 02:53.542
CAN YOU JUST THINK ABOUT IT
FOR A SECOND?

02:53.542 --> 02:56.041
EVERY MORNING,
YOU GET OUT OF BED,

02:56.041 --> 02:59.083
PUT TWO FEET ON THE GROUND,
AND STAND UP...

02:59.083 --> 03:01.500
LIKE IT'S EASY,
LIKE IT'S NOTHING.

03:01.500 --> 03:04.083
YOU PUT YOUR PANTS ON
ONE LEG AT A TIME.

03:04.083 --> 03:06.166
I MEAN,
IT'S SUCH A BASIC CONCEPT

03:06.166 --> 03:08.041
IT'S LITERALLY
AN EXPRESSION.

03:08.041 --> 03:11.583
IT MEANS YOU'RE JUST LIKE
EVERYBODY ELSE.

03:11.583 --> 03:13.417
EXCEPT ME AND JORDI --

03:13.417 --> 03:15.375
WE'RE NOT LIKE
ANYBODY ELSE.

03:15.375 --> 03:17.166
OH, SO HAVING CANCER
GIVES YOU THE RIGHT

03:17.166 --> 03:19.250
TO HURL GOLF BALLS
IN ANY DIRECTION,

03:19.250 --> 03:21.875
CAUSING POTENTIAL HEAD WOUNDS
ON UNSUSPECTING ANGELENOS?

03:21.875 --> 03:23.667
I'M JUST SAYING
TODAY'S ALL ABOUT JORDI,

03:23.667 --> 03:25.333
AND WE NEED TO BE THERE
FOR HIM.

03:25.333 --> 03:27.250
YEAH, WELL, I HAVE A STRESS TEST
TO WORRY ABOUT.

03:28.000 --> 03:30.333
LATER, LOSERS.

03:30.333 --> 03:32.500
<i>WITH KARA,</i>
<i>WHAT THEY SHOULD MEASURE</i>

03:32.500 --> 03:36.083
<i>IS HOW MUCH STRESS SHE CAUSES</i>
<i>OTHER PEOPLE.</i>

03:36.083 --> 03:37.667
Kenji:
DIDN'T YOU JUST GO HOME?

03:37.667 --> 03:38.709
WHAT ARE YOU DOING BACK?

03:38.709 --> 03:40.375
I MISSED YOU.

03:40.375 --> 03:42.125
-MM-HMM.
-[ CHUCKLES ]

03:42.125 --> 03:44.208
SOMEONE FELL OUT,

03:44.208 --> 03:45.542
AND WHEN I FIND OUT
WHO THAT SOMEONE IS...

03:45.542 --> 03:47.208
I WILL HAVE THEM KILLED.

03:47.208 --> 03:48.583
MM-HMM.

03:48.583 --> 03:51.417
HEY.
HAVE YOU SEEN LEO?

03:51.417 --> 03:53.500
HE'S SUPPOSED TO BE UPSTAIRS
WORKING THE NEW LEG,

03:53.500 --> 03:55.792
-BUT THE P.T. SAYS
HE HASN'T SHOWN UP.
-YEAH, I KNOW.

03:55.792 --> 03:57.625
HE'S WAITING FOR JORDI
TO WAKE UP FROM SURGERY.

03:57.625 --> 03:59.792
-KENJI!
-I'M SORRY.

03:59.792 --> 04:01.458
LOOK,
I TRIED TO GET HIM TO GO,

04:01.458 --> 04:04.000
BUT HE LOOKED AT ME
WITH THE EYES AND THE EYEBROWS

04:04.000 --> 04:05.667
AND THAT LITTLE BALD HEAD.

04:05.667 --> 04:07.792
YOU CAN'T LET A LITTLE BALD HEAD
INTERFERE WITH YOUR JOB.

04:07.792 --> 04:10.625
WE GOT A LOT OF LITTLE BALD
HEADS RUNNING AROUND THIS PLACE.

04:10.625 --> 04:12.625
IT'S
OUR RESPONSIBILITY

04:12.625 --> 04:15.625
TO SET HEALTHY BOUNDARIES
FOR THESE CHILDREN.

04:15.625 --> 04:18.417
TWO WORDS -- MONKEY LOVE.

04:18.417 --> 04:20.291
I'M GONNA NEED
MORE THAN TWO WORDS.

04:20.291 --> 04:21.834
WELL, TECHNICALLY,
IT'S A STUDY.

04:21.834 --> 04:23.333
AND THERE ARE MONKEYS
INVOLVED.

04:23.333 --> 04:25.000
-MORE. FASTER.
-WELL, THEY GAVE THE MONKEYS

04:25.000 --> 04:27.500
TWO DUMMY PARENTS -- ONE
FOR FEEDING AND ONE FOR HUGGING.

04:27.500 --> 04:29.458
-MM-HMM.
-AND EVEN THOUGH
THE FEEDING PARENTS

04:29.458 --> 04:31.208
WERE SEEMINGLY
MORE IMPORTANT,

04:31.208 --> 04:33.291
THE MONKEYS ALMOST ALWAYS CHOSE
THE HUGGING ONE.

04:33.291 --> 04:35.500
'CAUSE, YOU KNOW, THE LOVE.

04:35.500 --> 04:39.083
SO, I'M THE FOOD
IN THIS SCENARIO.

04:39.083 --> 04:40.417
YES.

04:40.417 --> 04:42.250
AND YOU'RE THE LOVE.

04:42.250 --> 04:43.667
WELL, IT'S A THEORY.

04:43.667 --> 04:45.667
I'M NOT SAYING
IT'S PERFECT.

04:45.667 --> 04:47.417
-[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
-MM-HMM.
OKAY, WELL, HERE'S MY THEORY --

04:47.417 --> 04:50.250
STARVING MONKEYS DIE.

04:50.250 --> 04:51.792
YOU MAKE A STRONG POINT.

04:58.000 --> 04:59.417
CHECK THIS OUT.

05:01.166 --> 05:03.667
ALPHA BETA BALL SACK,
MAN.

05:05.792 --> 05:09.667
MUST BE A GAME DAY.

05:17.458 --> 05:20.208
YO, IS IT ME OR DO THEY ALL LOOK
EXACTLY THE SAME?

05:20.208 --> 05:24.208
SAME STUPID HAIR,
SAME STUPID CLOTHES --

05:24.208 --> 05:26.291
LOOKS LIKE SOMEBODY 'ROIDED UP
ONE DIRECTION

05:26.291 --> 05:28.625
AND MATED THEM
WITH ZOMBIES.

05:28.625 --> 05:30.417
I THINK
THAT'S KIND OF THE POINT --

05:30.417 --> 05:31.792
YOU KNOW, SAFETY IN NUMBERS,
PACK MENTALITY.

05:31.792 --> 05:33.625
IT'S NOT THE WORST THING
EVER.

05:33.625 --> 05:35.875
YO, MAN, YOU KNOW I'M NOT
CALLING<i> YOU </i>STUPID, RIGHT?

05:35.875 --> 05:37.667
HEY, I PROBABLY WAS,
BUT WHATEVER.

05:37.667 --> 05:39.834
IT DOESN'T MATTER ANYMORE.

05:39.834 --> 05:41.291
LEO ROTH.

05:41.291 --> 05:43.166
YOU'RE LATE
FOR PHYSICAL THERAPY.

05:43.166 --> 05:45.625
DID YOU FORGET WHAT
FLOOR IT'S ON, BECAUSE
I'M HAPPY TO ESCORT YOU.

05:45.625 --> 05:48.375
-AS SOON AS HE'S OUT,
I'LL GO.
-THAT'S NOT HOW THIS WORKS.

05:48.375 --> 05:50.208
I TRIED TO TELL HIM,

05:50.208 --> 05:53.291
BUT THE YOUNG MAN DOES NOT HAVE
HIS LISTENING EARS ON TODAY.

05:53.291 --> 05:54.417
THIS IS YOU HELPING?

05:54.417 --> 05:57.166
DIVERTING ATTENTION.
STRATEGY.

05:57.166 --> 05:59.792
LOOK, I KNOW THE NEW LEG
IS UNCOMFORTABLE --

05:59.792 --> 06:01.375
[ CHUCKLES ] IT'S MORE
THAN UNCOMFORTABLE. IT HURTS.

06:01.375 --> 06:02.834
I DON'T LIKE
WALKING IN IT.

06:02.834 --> 06:04.792
THAT'S BECAUSE YOU HAVEN'T HAD
ENOUGH PRACTICE.

06:04.792 --> 06:07.250
JORDI'S GONNA BE UNCONSCIOUS
FOR THE NEXT FEW HOURS,

06:07.250 --> 06:09.625
SO THERE'S NO POINT
IN YOU HANGING AROUND HERE.

06:09.625 --> 06:11.875
YOU NEED TO BE UPSTAIRS
RIGHT NOW.

06:11.875 --> 06:13.291
NO, I NEED TO BE HERE.

06:13.291 --> 06:15.542
JORDI'S ENTIRE LIFE
IS ABOUT TO CHANGE,

06:15.542 --> 06:16.917
AND I'M THE ONLY ONE
WHO KNOWS

06:16.917 --> 06:18.917
JUST HOW MUCH
AND HOW BAD IT'S GONNA BE,

06:18.917 --> 06:21.709
SO I PLAN ON BEING THE FIRST
FACE HE SEES WHEN HIS EYES OPEN,

06:21.709 --> 06:23.333
BECAUSE THAT WAS THE DEAL
WE MADE.

06:25.750 --> 06:27.542
OKAY?

06:29.834 --> 06:32.333
I'M RESCHEDULING YOU
FOR 5:00.

06:32.333 --> 06:35.208
-NURSE JACKSON --
-THAT'S MY FINAL OFFER.

06:35.208 --> 06:37.333
TOUGH LOVE.

06:37.333 --> 06:39.083
[ SCOFFS ]

06:39.083 --> 06:41.792
♪ COME SO FAR ♪

06:41.792 --> 06:47.750
♪ FEEL SO REAL ♪

06:49.750 --> 06:52.333
[ LAUGHS ]

06:52.333 --> 06:54.917
♪ ALL THIS TIME ♪

06:54.917 --> 06:56.375
THANKS FOR CLEARING THAT UP
FOR ME.

06:56.375 --> 06:58.959
[ CHUCKLES ] I DIDN'T WANT
TO TAKE ANY CHANCES.

06:58.959 --> 07:00.667
HERE'S
WHAT'S HAPPENING NOW.

07:00.667 --> 07:02.500
WE'RE WAITING FOR THE BLOOD BANK
TO GET THEIR ACT TOGETHER,

07:02.500 --> 07:04.250
THEN THE ANESTHESIOLOGIST
IS GONNA COME IN HERE,

07:04.250 --> 07:06.041
AND HE'S GONNA DO
HIS THING.

07:06.041 --> 07:08.458
BUT WHILE THAT'S HAPPENING, I
WANT YOU TO DO SOMETHING FOR ME.

07:08.458 --> 07:10.750
WHAT IS IT?

07:10.750 --> 07:13.000
I NEED YOU TO PICK
A HAPPY MEMORY.

07:13.000 --> 07:15.583
ALL RIGHT? SOMETIME IN YOUR LIFE
WHERE EVERYTHING WENT RIGHT.

07:15.583 --> 07:16.834
YOU THINK
YOU CAN DO THAT?

07:16.834 --> 07:19.583
I'M ON IT.
GOOD.

07:23.125 --> 07:24.750
EMMA, HUH?

07:36.333 --> 07:38.667
<i>SO, JORDI'S THINKING</i>
<i>ABOUT EMMA,</i>

07:38.667 --> 07:41.291
<i>BUT SOMETHING ELSE IS</i>
<i>WEIGHING ON EMMA'S MIND.</i>

07:41.291 --> 07:42.834
TIME FOR YOUR WEIGH-IN.

07:42.834 --> 07:44.417
<i>SEE WHAT I DID THERE?</i>

07:44.417 --> 07:45.750
I JUST NEED TO BRUSH
MY TEETH.

07:45.750 --> 07:47.542
OH, DON'T FORGET TO BRUSH
YOUR TONGUE.

07:47.542 --> 07:49.375
THAT'S WHERE
THE BACTERIA LIVE.

08:04.250 --> 08:21.333
♪ OH-OH, OH-OH,
OH-OH, OH-OH ♪

08:21.333 --> 08:26.875
♪ WELL, SWIM WITH ME, WELL,
WE WILL GO FAR INTO THE SEA ♪

08:26.875 --> 08:29.750
♪ YOU WILL TAKE ME
ONTO YOUR BACK ♪

08:29.750 --> 08:33.000
♪ NEVER LOOK BACK,
NEVER LOOK BACK ♪

08:33.000 --> 08:37.125
♪ WELL, SING TO ME WELL,
SING ME A SONG, ♪

08:37.125 --> 08:44.000
♪ TELL ME THAT THINGS
NEVER GO WRONG ♪

08:44.000 --> 08:46.083
Woman: ARE YOU SURE
YOU DON'T WANT ANY WATER?

08:46.083 --> 08:48.709
ARE YOU SURE YOU WANT
TO KEEP ASKING ME THAT
EVERY FIVE SECONDS?

08:48.709 --> 08:50.583
BECAUSE IT'S NOT
REMOTELY ANNOYING.

08:50.583 --> 08:52.750
YOU'RE DOING GREAT, KARA. WE'RE
READY TO PICK UP THE PACE NOW.

08:52.750 --> 08:54.625
JUST BECAUSE<i> YOU'RE </i>READY
DOESN'T MEAN<i> I'M </i>READY.

08:54.625 --> 08:56.500
I'M ONLY TWO DAYS
INTO A BLOWOUT,

08:56.500 --> 08:59.667
AND A SINGLE BEAD OF NECK SWEAT
COULD CAUSE A FULL-ON FRIZZ,

08:59.667 --> 09:01.166
AND THEN YOU'D OWE ME
60 BUCKS.

09:01.166 --> 09:02.667
SHE'S A GENEROUS TIPPER.

09:02.667 --> 09:04.625
THE STRESS TEST IS MEANT
TO GATHER INFORMATION

09:04.625 --> 09:06.875
ABOUT HOW WELL YOUR HEART WORKS
DURING PHYSICAL ACTIVITY,

09:06.875 --> 09:09.458
ASSUMING YOU HAVE A HEART.

09:09.458 --> 09:13.041
BITING SARCASM
FROM THE GUY WEARING CROCS.

09:13.041 --> 09:17.000
<i>LIKE I SAID, IT ALWAYS COMES</i>
<i>BACK TO THE SHOES.</i>

09:17.000 --> 09:18.583
SO, DR. SAMUELS SAYS
I CAN GO

09:18.583 --> 09:20.542
TO THIS THEORETICAL PHYSICS
PROGRAM AT YALE THIS SUMMER

09:20.542 --> 09:22.625
IF I GAIN 10 POUNDS.
Brittany: OH.

09:22.625 --> 09:26.583
WE'VE BEEN TALKING ABOUT IT
A LOT DURING THERAPY.
OH.

09:26.583 --> 09:30.917
OKAY.
READY WHEN YOU ARE.

09:37.542 --> 09:39.875
[ GASPS ]
LOOK AT THAT!

09:39.875 --> 09:41.917
YOU GAINED A POUND.

09:41.917 --> 09:44.417
GOOD WORK, EMMA.

09:44.417 --> 09:47.709
I AM SO PROUD OF YOU.

09:47.709 --> 09:49.542
YEAH, WE'RE DONE HERE.

09:49.542 --> 09:52.333
STAY.

09:52.333 --> 09:55.083
Kara: SO, GAINED A FULL POUND,
HUH?

09:55.083 --> 09:56.625
THAT'S EXCITING.

09:56.625 --> 09:59.333
YOU KNOW, THE QUEEN OF ENGLAND
USED TO SEW WEIGHTS

09:59.333 --> 10:01.709
TO THE HEMS OF HER DRESSES
TO KEEP THEM FROM BLOWING
UP IN THE WIND.

10:01.709 --> 10:03.542
I GOT THE NEEDLE
IF YOU GOT THE THREAD.

10:03.542 --> 10:05.583
I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

10:05.583 --> 10:07.834
-SURE YOU DON'T.
-Kenji: OH, GOOD. THERE YOU ARE.

10:07.834 --> 10:09.291
YOU HAVE VISITORS, KARA.

10:09.291 --> 10:11.375
IS IT BRADY? COURTNEY?

10:11.375 --> 10:12.208
IT'S YOUR MOMS.

10:20.375 --> 10:22.583
ALL RIGHT. YOU GOT THAT MEMORY
PICKED OUT?

10:22.583 --> 10:23.750
Jordi: I THINK SO.

10:23.750 --> 10:26.417
BACK IN MEXICO,
I WON MY SCHOOL'S TALENT SHOW.

10:26.417 --> 10:27.792
I SANG THIS SONG I WROTE.

10:27.792 --> 10:30.166
-IT WAS PRETTY COOL.
-I LIKE THAT.

10:31.959 --> 10:33.709
OKAY, WE'RE GONNA START
THE INDUCTION NOW,

10:33.709 --> 10:35.625
AND I WANT YOU TO FOCUS
ON THAT SONG.

10:35.625 --> 10:38.500
IT'LL KEEP YOU IN A GOOD PLACE
DURING SURGERY, OKAY?

10:38.500 --> 10:41.208
ALL RIGHT. ON MY COUNT --

10:41.208 --> 10:44.625
-NINE...EIGHT...
-[ GUITAR PLAYS ]

10:44.625 --> 10:46.959
SEVEN...

10:46.959 --> 10:49.458
SIX...

10:49.458 --> 10:54.375
-Jordi: ♪ JUST A LITTLE BOY
SKIPPING ROCKS BY THE RIVER♪
-...FIVE...

10:54.375 --> 10:59.750
♪ A HUNDRED YARDS
OFF THE GRAVEL ROAD ♪

10:59.750 --> 11:05.542
♪ SKIPPING SCHOOL,
A LIFE WE ALL IMAGINE ♪

11:05.542 --> 11:08.875
♪ DAYS WENT BY,
WE'D HARDLY EVEN KNOW ♪

11:08.875 --> 11:10.834
HEY, JORDI!

11:10.834 --> 11:13.041
DOWN HERE.

11:13.041 --> 11:15.333
SORRY, I DIDN'T MEAN
TO INTERRUPT YOUR SONG.

11:15.333 --> 11:17.667
IT'S JUST I WASN'T SURE
HOW MUCH TIME WE HAVE.

11:17.667 --> 11:19.041
I'M CHARLIE.

11:19.041 --> 11:20.875
I-I WAS IN SURGERY.

11:20.875 --> 11:22.208
YOU STILL ARE.

11:22.208 --> 11:24.792
THIS IS
JUST A MENTAL BREAK.

11:24.792 --> 11:26.667
CAN I INTEREST YOU
IN SOME CHECKERS,

11:26.667 --> 11:28.750
OR ARE YOU MORE
OF A BOGGLE KIND OF GUY?

11:28.750 --> 11:31.083
-YOU'RE THE KID IN THE COMA.
-YEAH.

11:31.083 --> 11:33.000
UNFORTUNATELY,
THAT HAS BECOME

11:33.000 --> 11:35.250
MY MOST IDENTIFIABLE
CHARACTERISTIC.

11:35.250 --> 11:38.333
-AM I DEAD?
-NO. NO, YOU'RE NOT DEAD.

11:38.333 --> 11:40.458
I'M HERE TO HELP YOU
TAKE YOUR MIND OFF THINGS

11:40.458 --> 11:42.709
WHILE THEY FIX YOU
OUT THERE.

11:42.709 --> 11:45.875
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

11:45.875 --> 11:47.375
ARE YOU OKAY?

11:47.375 --> 11:49.333
WHAT'S HAPPENING TO ME?

11:49.333 --> 11:50.542
I FEEL DIZZY.

11:50.542 --> 11:51.667
WHY AM I DIZZY?

11:54.125 --> 11:56.959
I'M RIGHT HERE, JORDI.
RIGHT HERE.

11:56.959 --> 11:58.542
Charlie: JORDI?

11:58.542 --> 11:59.125
DAMN IT.

11:59.125 --> 12:01.542
THERE IS SIGNIFICANT SOFT TISSUE
INVOLVEMENT.

12:01.542 --> 12:03.291
IT'S EXTENDING FURTHER
PROXIMALLY

12:03.291 --> 12:04.583
-ARE WE STILL GOING AHEAD
WITH THE A.K.A.?
-NO.

12:04.583 --> 12:08.500
NEW PLAN, GET THIS SAMPLE TO
PATH FOR A FROZEN SECTION, NOW.

12:08.500 --> 12:10.166
LOOKS LIKE HIS CANCER HAS SPREAD

12:13.667 --> 12:15.750
<i>SO, IF YOU'RE JUST CHECKING IN,</i>

12:15.750 --> 12:17.959
<i>THESE ARE KARA'S MOMS,</i>
<i>SARAH AND DANIELLA.</i>

12:17.959 --> 12:19.542
SO SORRY, KARA BEAR.

12:19.542 --> 12:22.208
WE NEVER WOULD HAVE GONE TO CABO
IF WE'D HAVE KNOWN.

12:22.208 --> 12:25.375
IT WAS JUST KIND OF A CRAZY,
SPUR-OF-THE-MOMENT THING.

12:25.375 --> 12:26.959
YEAH,
SO WAS MY HEART ATTACK.

12:26.959 --> 12:29.417
THEY EXPLAINED IT
AS SOME KIND OF CARDIAC EVENT?

12:29.417 --> 12:30.709
SHE HAS AN ENLARGED HEART.

12:30.709 --> 12:32.083
THAT'S WHAT WE'RE DEALING WITH,
RIGHT?

12:32.083 --> 12:33.917
UH, YEAH.

12:33.917 --> 12:35.750
I CAN HAVE A DOCTOR COME
IN AND TAKE YOU THROUGH
IT, IF YOU LIKE.

12:35.750 --> 12:37.375
[ SCOFFS ] LIKE I'M GONNA ENDURE
THAT AGAIN.

12:37.375 --> 12:39.250
E-MAIL IT TO HER.

12:39.250 --> 12:41.166
LOOK, I'M SORRY
THAT I INTERRUPTED

12:41.166 --> 12:43.500
YOUR ROMANTIC GETAWAY
WITH MY NANNY.

12:43.500 --> 12:46.333
<i>WHAT? DADS FALL FOR THE NANNY</i>
<i>ALL THE TIME.</i>

12:46.333 --> 12:48.000
<i>WHY NOT MOMS?</i>

12:48.000 --> 12:49.917
I REALLY WISH YOU WOULDN'T SAY
STUFF LIKE THAT, KARA.

12:49.917 --> 12:51.291
YOUR MOM AND I ARE MARRIED
NOW.

12:51.291 --> 12:53.458
WE'RE -- WE'RE FAMILY.

12:53.458 --> 12:56.208
THANKS FOR THE REMINDER, BUT
YOU'LL ALWAYS BE THE HELP TO ME.

12:56.208 --> 12:58.041
Sarah: YOU BEST CAP
THAT ATTITUDE, YOUNG LADY.

12:58.041 --> 12:59.917
WE NEED TO FOCUS
ON THE MATTER AT HAND,

12:59.917 --> 13:02.083
WHICH IS GETTING YOU
A BRAND-NEW HEART.

13:02.083 --> 13:03.959
DO YOU TAKE PLASTIC?
SMART. GET THE MILES.

13:03.959 --> 13:05.125
MM.
MOM!

13:05.125 --> 13:06.500
DOESN'T QUITE WORK
THAT WAY.

13:06.500 --> 13:08.333
Sarah:
WELL, IF IT'S ABOUT CONNECTIONS,

13:08.333 --> 13:10.083
JUST TELL US
WHO WE NEED TO TALK TO.

13:10.083 --> 13:12.291
WE SHARE A TRAINER
WITH ELLEN AND PORTIA.

13:12.291 --> 13:14.792
WE COULD GET YOU TICKETS TO
HER SHOW. IT'S EVEN BETTER LIVE.

13:14.792 --> 13:17.250
EVERYTHING YOU'RE SAYING IS
AMAZING ON A NUMBER OF LEVELS.

13:17.250 --> 13:20.166
HOWEVER, IN ORDER FOR
YOUR DAUGHTER TO GET ON
THE WAIT LIST FOR A HEART,

13:20.166 --> 13:22.959
HER CASE FIRST NEEDS TO BE
REVIEWED BY THE TRANSPLANT TEAM.

13:22.959 --> 13:24.875
WAIT, WHAT?
MOM, WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

13:24.875 --> 13:27.291
-DO I HAVE TO, LIKE, DO STUFF?
-LET ME HANDLE THIS.

13:27.291 --> 13:30.792
I KNOW THERE'S A LIST,
BUT THERE'S ALSO<i> THE </i>LIST.

13:30.792 --> 13:32.542
WHAT DO PEOPLE LIKE US
DO?

13:32.542 --> 13:35.375
YOU GET ON THE LIST.
THERE'S ONLY ONE.

13:35.375 --> 13:36.959
PREFERENTIAL TREATMENT
DOESN'T EXIST

13:36.959 --> 13:39.208
-IN THE ORGAN-DONATION
COMMUNITY.
-LISTEN, GIRLFRIEND,

13:39.208 --> 13:41.041
WE DIDN'T BECOME
<i>OUT </i>MAGAZINE'S

13:41.041 --> 13:43.625
SEVENTH MOST POWERFUL LESBIAN
COUPLE IN SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA

13:43.625 --> 13:45.208
BY WORKING OUR WAY UP
A FREAKIN' LIST.

13:45.208 --> 13:47.083
NOW TELL ME
WHO I HAVE TO CALL

13:47.083 --> 13:48.500
TO GET A QUALITY TICKER
AROUND HERE.

13:49.834 --> 13:51.792
THIS IS GONNA BE
A FUN DAY.

13:54.125 --> 13:55.667
WELL, THAT WAS RUDE.

13:59.250 --> 14:00.917
-HEY.
-GOOD MORNING.

14:00.917 --> 14:03.041
OH, ALTHOUGH TECHNICALLY,
I GUESS IT'S AFTERNOON.

14:03.041 --> 14:04.792
IT DEPENDS ON
WHEN YOU EAT LUNCH, RIGHT?

14:04.792 --> 14:06.750
I'VE ALWAYS BEEN
MORE OF A NOON KIND OF GAL.

14:06.750 --> 14:08.583
I'M IN A HURRY.
OH, RIGHT.

14:08.583 --> 14:10.208
UH, I JUST WANTED TO SHARE
SOME GREAT NEWS.

14:10.208 --> 14:11.959
EMMA GAINED WEIGHT.

14:11.959 --> 14:14.291
-SINCE WHEN?
-SINCE TODAY.

14:14.291 --> 14:17.166
DON'T WORRY. I WAS ENCOURAGING
BUT TOUGH ON HER.

14:17.166 --> 14:19.083
I JUST ASKED MYSELF.
"WWNJD?"

14:20.083 --> 14:21.458
"WHAT WOULD NURSE JACKSON
DO?"

14:21.458 --> 14:25.000
NURSE JACKSON. N.J.
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:25.000 --> 14:27.500
HERE'S WHAT N.J. WOULD DO --
SHE'D CHECK EMMA'S POCKETS,

14:27.500 --> 14:29.125
SUBTRACT THE WEIGHT
OF HER CLOTHES,

14:29.125 --> 14:30.417
CONSIDER HER FOOD INTAKE
THE LAST WEEK,

14:30.417 --> 14:32.458
WHICH IS IN NO WAY CONSISTENT
WITH A GAIN.

14:32.458 --> 14:33.917
DID YOU DO ANY OF THAT?

14:33.917 --> 14:35.583
UM, NO.

14:35.583 --> 14:37.458
DIDN'T THINK SO.

14:37.458 --> 14:38.875
ADJUST HER WEIGHT
ON THE CHART.

14:38.875 --> 14:41.083
MONKEY LOVE MY ASS.

14:49.166 --> 14:50.125
HI.

14:50.125 --> 14:51.625
HEY.

14:53.041 --> 14:56.709
HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON, DASH?
HOW ARE YOU?

14:56.709 --> 14:59.125
NOTHING MUCH. JUST CHILLING.
LIVING. YOU?

14:59.125 --> 15:00.291
HI, DASH.

15:00.291 --> 15:01.709
OH, HEY. HOW ARE YOU?

15:01.709 --> 15:04.250
SO, IS HE STILL IN SURGERY?

15:04.250 --> 15:06.792
HE IS.
NO WORD YET.

15:14.959 --> 15:17.667
THAT'S NOT THE BAND I GAVE YOU
LAST NIGHT.

15:17.667 --> 15:21.375
YEAH, UM...I-I LOST THE ONE
THAT YOU GAVE ME.

15:21.375 --> 15:23.000
IT SLIPPED OFF
OF MY WRIST.

15:23.000 --> 15:26.041
SO, WHO GAVE YOU --
JORDI.

15:26.041 --> 15:27.333
DAMN!

15:29.166 --> 15:31.458
OH. MY BAD.

15:31.458 --> 15:33.500
I MEAN...DAMN.

15:33.500 --> 15:34.875
OH, GOOD.
YOU'RE ALL HERE.

15:34.875 --> 15:36.667
HOW DID IT GO?
IS HE OKAY?

15:36.667 --> 15:38.750
JORDI'S IN RECOVERY.
HE'S GOOD.

15:38.750 --> 15:41.083
HE DID, UH --
HE DID REAL WELL.

15:41.083 --> 15:43.375
-SO, CAN WE SEE HIM?
-UH, HE'S STILL UNDER,

15:43.375 --> 15:45.709
SO IT SHOULDN'T BE
TOO MUCH LONGER.

15:45.709 --> 15:50.917
DO YOU GUYS MIND IF I TALK
TO LEO FOR A SECOND IN PRIVATE?

15:50.917 --> 15:51.667
<i>IN A HOSPITAL,</i>

15:51.667 --> 15:54.166
<i>WHENEVER SOMEONE SAYS THEY WANT</i>
<i>TO TALK TO YOU IN PRIVATE,</i>

15:54.166 --> 15:55.709
<i>IT'S NEVER GOOD NEWS.</i>

15:55.709 --> 15:58.417
-HEY. [ CLEARS THROAT ]
-WHAT'S UP?

15:58.417 --> 16:00.458
ALL RIGHT,
LOOK, AS YOU KNOW,

16:00.458 --> 16:03.709
NO TWO CASES,
NO TWO TUMORS ARE THE SAME.

16:03.709 --> 16:06.417
EVEN IF THINGS SEEM SIMILAR
ON THE OUTSET,

16:06.417 --> 16:10.583
WE NEVER KNOW WHAT WE'RE GONNA
FIND UNTIL WE GET IN THERE.

16:10.583 --> 16:13.458
IN JORDI'S CASE, IT WAS
A LITTLE MORE COMPLICATED
THAN WE EXPECTED,

16:13.458 --> 16:17.083
AND I DIDN'T DO THE SURGERY
THAT I WENT IN TO DO.

16:18.625 --> 16:21.291
UH, MEANING WHAT?

16:25.041 --> 16:28.709
OH.

16:28.709 --> 16:30.208
YOU DIDN'T CUT OFF HIS LEG,
DID YOU?

16:30.959 --> 16:31.750
NO, BUT --

16:31.750 --> 16:34.166
DID JORDI GET TO KEEP
HIS LEG?

16:45.917 --> 16:48.000
<i>ONE OF THE HARDEST THINGS</i>
<i>IN A HOSPITAL</i>

16:48.000 --> 16:52.125
<i>IS TO HAVE SOMEONE ELSE GET</i>
<i>EXACTLY WHAT YOU WANTED.</i>

17:00.333 --> 17:02.625
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU DID
"SAD."

17:02.625 --> 17:04.375
I'M HAVING
KIND OF A CRAP DAY.

17:04.375 --> 17:06.792
SORRY FOR CURSING.

17:09.500 --> 17:11.333
ALL RIGHT.
WHAT HAPPENED?

17:13.208 --> 17:15.333
I MESSED UP
EMMA'S WEIGH-IN.

17:15.333 --> 17:20.125
AND NOW NURSE JACKSON,
WHO ALREADY THINKS I'M USELESS,

17:20.125 --> 17:21.625
DOESN'T TRUST ME
TO DO ANYTHING.

17:21.625 --> 17:22.834
SHE WOULDN'T EVEN LET ME
TAKE A KID'S BLOOD PRESSURE.

17:22.834 --> 17:24.333
SHE'LL EASE UP EVENTUALLY.

17:24.333 --> 17:26.250
WELL,
MAYBE SHE SHOULDN'T.

17:26.250 --> 17:27.542
MAYBE SHE'S RIGHT.

17:27.542 --> 17:29.041
WHAT IF I SUCK AT THIS?

17:29.041 --> 17:31.041
AND WHAT IF YOU DON'T?

17:31.041 --> 17:35.375
ARE YOU REALLY PREPARED TO LET
ME SCREW UP SOME SICK KID'S LIFE

17:35.375 --> 17:37.417
ON THE OFF CHANCE
THAT I WON'T CONTINUE TO SUCK?

17:37.417 --> 17:39.750
I MEAN, IT'S NOT LIKE
BEING BAD AT REAL ESTATE.

17:39.750 --> 17:42.875
WORST-CASE SCENARIO,
A BAD REALTOR CAN'T KILL ANYONE.

17:42.875 --> 17:46.041
IT WOULD BE VERY DIFFICULT FOR
YOU TO KILL ANYONE, BRITTANY.

17:46.041 --> 17:47.375
LOOK,
I HEAR WHAT YOU'RE SAYING.

17:47.375 --> 17:49.500
SOME DAYS, I WISH I'D FOLLOWED
MY FATHER INTO FINANCE.

17:49.500 --> 17:51.750
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?
MY HEART WOULDN'T BE IN IT.

17:51.750 --> 17:53.000
THIS IS A CALLING.

17:53.000 --> 17:55.417
I'M NOT SURE
<i>I </i>GOT THE CALL.

17:55.417 --> 17:57.875
IF I DID, IT WASN'T LIKE,
"911. WE NEED YOU!"

17:57.875 --> 17:59.417
-[ PAGER BEEPING ]
-IT WAS MORE LIKE, YOU KNOW,
"HEY, BRIT.

17:59.417 --> 18:01.750
-WHAT'S UP?
YOU WANT TO COME OVER?"
-I GOT TO GO.

18:01.750 --> 18:03.458
OH.

18:03.458 --> 18:07.125
[ SIGHS ]

18:10.166 --> 18:12.083
<i>HOW DO YOU TELL A KID, </i>
<i>WITH NO PARENTS,</i>

18:12.083 --> 18:14.709
<i>WHO DROVE ACROSS THE BORDER </i>
<i>TO BE SAVED</i>

18:14.709 --> 18:17.375
<i>THAT YOU MIGHT NOT</i>
<i>BE ABLE TO SAVE HIM?</i>

18:17.375 --> 18:19.625
[ SIGHS ]

18:21.959 --> 18:24.166
I THINK OUR FIRST ORDER OF
BUSINESS IS TO RAISE AWARENESS,

18:24.166 --> 18:26.000
GO VIRAL --
INSTAGRAM, TWITTER, VINE,

18:26.000 --> 18:27.750
AND THEN A HASHTAG
TO PUT IT TO BED.

18:27.750 --> 18:29.333
-WELL, WHAT ABOUT AN EVENT?
-TALK TO ME.

18:29.333 --> 18:31.709
TWO WORDS -- SOUL CYCLE.

18:31.709 --> 18:33.458
I'M LISTENING.

18:33.458 --> 18:35.625
DO YOU REMEMBER WHEN JEN HAD
THE EVENT AT THE BEVERLY HILTON?

18:35.625 --> 18:37.375
Sarah: WITH ALL THAT NONSENSE
ON HER FACE?

18:37.375 --> 18:40.000
<i>I'VE NEVER SEEN KARA</i>
<i>THIS QUIET.</i>

18:40.000 --> 18:41.709
<i>YOU'D THINK IT WOULD BE</i>
<i>A WELCOME CHANGE,</i>

18:41.709 --> 18:44.083
<i>BUT IT'S KIND OF MAKING ME SAD,</i>

18:44.083 --> 18:45.792
<i>AND I'M ALREADY IN A COMA.</i>

18:45.792 --> 18:47.834
<i>IT'S HARD TO BUM ME OUT.</i>

18:47.834 --> 18:49.375
-I THINK SHE WAS DRUNK.
[ CHUCKLES ]
-OH.

18:49.375 --> 18:51.542
-OKAY, BUT WHAT
WERE WE FIGHTING FOR?
-SHE'S SUCH A BITCH.

18:51.542 --> 18:53.166
NOT THAT YOU
HAVE TO TELL ME.

18:53.166 --> 18:55.417
YOU REMEMBER
RIDE FOR ROSACEA?
YES.

18:55.417 --> 18:57.208
PEOPLE LOVE TO SWEAT
FOR A GOOD CAUSE.

18:57.208 --> 18:58.750
BY THE TIME WE DISMOUNTED
THOSE BIKES,

18:58.750 --> 19:00.125
OUR SKIN HAD THE LUSTER
OF A FRESHWATER PEARL.

19:00.125 --> 19:02.250
I'VE GOT IT.
#HeartAndSoul.

19:02.250 --> 19:04.166
[ GASPS ] OH, MY GOD.
WRITE THAT DOWN.

19:04.166 --> 19:05.875
-WRITE THAT DOWN RIGHT NOW.
-AREYOU KIDDING ME?

19:05.875 --> 19:07.083
KARA, WHAT DO YOU THINK?

19:07.083 --> 19:09.208
OH. WH--

19:11.625 --> 19:13.917
-SHOULD WE GO LOOK FOR HER?
-IN A SECOND.

19:13.917 --> 19:15.208
THAT'S SO GOOD.

19:19.709 --> 19:22.917
YOU'RE TRYING MY SALTED-ICE-CUBE
DIET, AREN'T YOU?

19:22.917 --> 19:24.417
WHAT DO YOU WANT, KARA?

19:24.417 --> 19:26.542
IF YOU'RE LOOKING FOR CHILDREN'S
SOULS, TRY THE NICU.

19:26.542 --> 19:28.417
YOU HAVE A BUNCH OF WEEKLIES
I HAVEN'T READ YET.

19:28.417 --> 19:30.333
TAKE THEM.
THEY'RE ALL YOURS.

19:30.333 --> 19:32.458
Kara: I COULD ALSO USE
A QUIET PLACE TO READ THEM.

19:32.458 --> 19:33.583
I DON'T THINK SO.

19:33.583 --> 19:35.667
-WHY NOT?
-BECAUSE I DON'T LIKE YOU.

19:35.667 --> 19:37.291
SO?

19:37.291 --> 19:38.667
I CAN EAT YOUR LUNCH
FOR A WHOLE WEEK IF YOU WANT.

19:38.667 --> 19:41.583
AND THIS WAY,
NEXT TIME YOU "GAIN WEIGHT,"

19:41.583 --> 19:43.583
THEY MIGHT
ACTUALLY BELIEVE YOU.

19:43.583 --> 19:46.000
YOU CAN STAY IN MY ROOM
FOR 20 MINUTES

19:46.000 --> 19:47.625
IF YOU TELL ME
WHY YOU'RE REALLY HERE.

19:47.625 --> 19:48.750
WHAT DO YOU CARE WHY?

19:48.750 --> 19:51.250
I DON'T CARE.
BUT I'M TRYING.

19:51.250 --> 19:52.750
IT'S CALLED EMPATHY.

19:52.750 --> 19:54.417
OKAY, FINE.

19:54.417 --> 19:56.041
I'M AVOIDING NURSE JACKSON.

19:56.041 --> 19:58.250
SHE'S TOTALLY OUT TO GET ME
FOR, LIKE, NO REASON.

19:58.250 --> 20:00.917
BY NURSE JACKSON, DO YOU MEAN
YOUR POWER LESBIAN MOMS?

20:03.083 --> 20:05.125
WELL, SORRY WE DIDN'T
ALL GROW UP

20:05.125 --> 20:07.500
ON A VERY SPECIAL EPISODE
OF "7th HEAVEN."

20:11.792 --> 20:14.125
WHY DO YOU HAVE TO BE
LIKE THAT?

20:14.125 --> 20:15.542
LIKE YOU DON'T CARE?

20:15.542 --> 20:18.625
I MEAN, TRY BEING HONEST
FOR A CHANGE.

20:18.625 --> 20:20.792
YOU CAN START BY TELLING ME
ONE TRUE THING ABOUT YOURSELF.

20:20.792 --> 20:24.125
<i>SHE SNORES,</i>
<i>SHE HOARDS CHEETOS,</i>

20:24.125 --> 20:26.125
<i>THAT BLOWOUT OF HERS</i>
<i>IS ALL EXTENSIONS --</i>

20:26.125 --> 20:27.583
<i>I COULD GO ON.</i>

20:27.583 --> 20:28.834
CAN I ASK YOU
A QUESTION FIRST?

20:28.834 --> 20:30.417
DEPENDS HOW INSULTING IT IS.

20:30.417 --> 20:34.166
DID YOUR DAD SERIOUSLY MAKE YOU
WEAR THAT SHIRT?

20:34.166 --> 20:35.959
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:35.959 --> 20:38.291
HE DIDN'T MAKE ME.
I WANTED TO.

20:38.291 --> 20:40.834
WE HAD THEM MADE FOR OUR ANNUAL
MEMORIAL DAY CAMPING TRIP.

20:40.834 --> 20:45.291
SO, YOU, LIKE, DO STUFF WITH
YOUR PARENTS OUTSIDE OF THERAPY?

20:45.291 --> 20:47.458
WE USED TO DO
A LOT TOGETHER,

20:47.458 --> 20:48.959
BUT WHEN I GOT SICK,

20:48.959 --> 20:51.375
THEY BECAME TOTALLY FOCUSED
ON MY DISORDER --

20:51.375 --> 20:54.041
WHAT I WAS EATING,
HOW SKINNY I BECAME.

20:54.041 --> 20:57.333
EVERYTHING SHIFTED
FROM OUR FAMILY TO JUST...ME.

20:59.458 --> 21:01.792
THAT ACTUALLY SOUNDS NICE.

21:01.792 --> 21:06.083
MY MOM'S ONLY INTERESTED IN ME
WHEN IT BENEFITS HER.

21:11.500 --> 21:13.333
YOU JUST BOUGHT YOURSELF
20 MINUTES.

21:26.834 --> 21:29.709
DR. McANDREW.

21:29.709 --> 21:31.458
JORDI.

21:31.458 --> 21:33.583
HEY, MAN.
YOU DID GREAT.

21:33.583 --> 21:35.291
IT DOESN'T HURT
AS MUCH AS I THOUGHT.

21:35.291 --> 21:38.125
WELL, WE ENDED UP TAKING
A DIFFERENT ROUTE IN SURGERY.

21:38.125 --> 21:40.291
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

21:40.291 --> 21:42.792
I DID NOT TAKE OFF
YOUR LEG.

21:42.792 --> 21:46.250
WAIT, WHAT?

21:46.250 --> 21:48.917
OH, MY GOD.

21:48.917 --> 21:51.208
YOU SAVED MY LEG!

21:51.208 --> 21:52.542
THANK YOU!
[ Laughing ] THANK YOU SO MUCH!

21:52.542 --> 21:54.583
JORDI, JORDI --
OH.

21:54.583 --> 21:57.125
I THINK I FEEL LIKE
I'M GONNA THROW UP.

21:57.125 --> 21:59.041
ALL RIGHT. OKAY, LISTEN.
JUST CLOSE YOUR EYES.

21:59.041 --> 22:01.375
TAKE A DEEP BREATH.

22:01.375 --> 22:03.583
THERE YOU GO.

22:03.583 --> 22:06.083
WE'RE GONNA TALK ABOUT THIS
LATER, OKAY?

22:06.083 --> 22:08.083
<i>THE ONLY THING WORSE</i>
<i>THAN FINDING OUT</i>

22:08.083 --> 22:10.458
<i>THAT SOMEONE'S TEST RESULTS</i>
<i>ARE WORSE THAN YOU EXPECTED</i>

22:10.458 --> 22:12.875
<i>IS HAVING TO TELL THEM.</i>

22:15.875 --> 22:17.083
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN HERE?

22:17.083 --> 22:19.125
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

22:19.125 --> 22:20.542
SHE'S LEAVING
IN THREE MINUTES.

22:20.542 --> 22:22.041
I'LL COME BACK THEN.

22:22.041 --> 22:24.542
WAIT.
HAVE YOU SEEN JORDI?

22:24.542 --> 22:25.875
HOW IS HE?

22:25.875 --> 22:28.000
HE'S GREAT.
HE GOT TO KEEP HIS LEG.

22:28.000 --> 22:31.250
OH, MY GOD.
YOU MUST FEEL LIKE CRAP.

22:31.250 --> 22:32.625
LEO'S NOT LIKE THAT.

22:32.625 --> 22:34.291
I MEAN, OF COURSE HE'S HAPPY
FOR JORDI.

22:34.291 --> 22:35.917
OH, ARE YOU, LEO?

22:35.917 --> 22:38.542
ARE YOU SO, SO HAPPY FOR JORDI
RIGHT NOW?

22:38.542 --> 22:43.125
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

22:43.125 --> 22:44.333
DO YOU WORK HARD
TO BE THIS MEAN,

22:44.333 --> 22:45.875
OR DOES IT COME NATURALLY
TO YOU?

22:45.875 --> 22:47.542
I HAVE A BETTER QUESTION.

22:47.542 --> 22:50.083
WHY IS IT THAT
THE TWO MOST ELIGIBLE BACHELORS

22:50.083 --> 22:53.375
IN THIS HELLHOLE CAN ONLY
SPORT WOOD FOR A BAG OF BONES?

22:53.375 --> 22:54.917
YEAH, YOU CAN LEAVE NOW.

22:54.917 --> 22:56.500
GLADLY.

23:02.083 --> 23:03.917
[ GRUNTS ]

23:03.917 --> 23:06.250
[ SIGHS ]

23:06.250 --> 23:08.625
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?
I'M OUT OF HERE.

23:08.625 --> 23:10.667
WHERE TO?
SOMEWHERE NORMAL,

23:10.667 --> 23:12.625
A PLACE WHERE I CAN JUST BE
LIKE EVERYBODY ELSE.

23:12.625 --> 23:14.250
NOT WITHOUT ME, MAN.

23:14.250 --> 23:16.250
LOOK, I'M GONNA GET CHANGED
REAL QUICK.

23:16.250 --> 23:18.208
[ SIGHS ]

23:18.208 --> 23:20.709
<i>LOOKS LIKE LEO'S FINALLY</i>
<i>GONNA WALK A MILE...</i>

23:20.709 --> 23:22.625
<i>OR JUST ACROSS THE STREET.</i>

23:22.625 --> 23:28.291
♪ SOMETHING IS NOT RIGHT
WITH ME ♪

23:28.291 --> 23:30.583
♪ HOW WAS I SUPPOSED TO KNOW? ♪

23:30.583 --> 23:33.792
YOU KNOW, SOMETIMES THINGS
ARE BETTER IN THEORY THAN
THEY ARE IN PRACTICE.

23:33.792 --> 23:36.417
-THIS IS NOT
ONE OF THOSE TIMES.
-♪ SOMETHING IS NOT RIGHT

23:33.792 --> 23:38.125
WITH ME ♪

23:36.417 --> 23:38.125
♪ SOMETHING IS NOT RIGHT

23:38.125 --> 23:40.417
♪ HOW WAS I SUPPOSED TO KNOW? ♪

23:40.417 --> 23:46.917
♪ SOMETHING IS NOT RIGHT
WITH ME ♪

23:46.917 --> 23:50.500
♪ TRYING NOT TO LET IT SHOW♪

23:51.750 --> 23:55.166
SO, GETTING TO KEEP HIS LEG
WAS ACTUALLY A BAD THING?

23:55.166 --> 23:56.583
[ SIGHS ]
WELL, I'M STILL WAITING

23:56.583 --> 23:58.166
FOR THE ONC TEAM TO REVIEW
ALL THE PATH,

23:58.166 --> 24:00.375
BUT THIS IS
NOT AN OSTEOSARCOMA.

24:00.375 --> 24:02.667
-WHAT DOES JORDI KNOW?
-OH, MY GOD.

24:02.667 --> 24:04.917
HE WAS SO HAPPY HE GOT
TO KEEP HIS LEG, I COULDN'T --

24:04.917 --> 24:06.583
I COULDN'T GO THERE YET.

24:06.583 --> 24:08.458
HOW'S LEO TAKING IT?

24:08.458 --> 24:10.750
ABOUT AS WELL
AS YOU'D EXPECT.

24:10.750 --> 24:13.083
I SHOULD PROBABLY TALK TO LEO,
TOO.

24:13.083 --> 24:16.083
-[ SIGHS ]
-YOU OKAY?

24:16.083 --> 24:19.792
YEAH, YOU KNOW, USUALLY
I SEE 99 PATIENTS IN
A ROW AND I'M FINE.

24:19.792 --> 24:23.709
THIS KID COMES IN ALONE,
NO FAMILY,

24:23.709 --> 24:25.500
TRYING TO SAVE
HIS OWN LIFE,

24:25.500 --> 24:27.667
I MEAN,
IT JUST SNEAKS UP ON YOU.

24:27.667 --> 24:30.083
JUST FIGURE OUT HOW YOU'RE GONNA
BREAK THE NEWS TO JORDI.

24:30.083 --> 24:31.375
I'LL DEAL WITH LEO.

24:31.375 --> 24:32.542
NO,
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THAT.

24:32.542 --> 24:35.125
-I DON'T MIND.
-NO, REALLY. IT'S FINE.

24:35.125 --> 24:36.375
YOU DON'T WANT ME
TALKING TO LEO.

24:36.375 --> 24:38.792
WHAT?

24:38.792 --> 24:41.125
OF COURSE I DO.
I JUST -- I KNOW...

24:41.125 --> 24:42.792
I KNOW HOW BUSY YOU ARE.

24:42.792 --> 24:44.625
YOU THINK
I CAN'T BE NICE.

24:44.625 --> 24:47.375
I'D LIKE TO START OVER,
IF I MAY.

24:47.375 --> 24:51.000
I BET YOU WOULD...
JACKASS.

24:51.000 --> 24:54.125
SEE?
THAT...IS NOT NICE.

24:54.125 --> 24:56.458
[ UP-TEMPO POP MUSIC PLAYING ]

25:00.041 --> 25:02.583
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

25:02.583 --> 25:04.375
I JUST CAN'T BELIEVE

25:04.375 --> 25:06.166
THAT YOU'VE NEVER SEEN
"THE HUNGER GAMES."

25:06.166 --> 25:08.000
IT'S LIKE, SERIOUSLY,
THE GREATEST THING
THAT'S EVER HAPPENED.

25:08.000 --> 25:10.000
-WELL, THAT'S NOT POSSIBLE.
-WHY NOT?

25:10.000 --> 25:12.417
BECAUSE<i> YOU'RE </i>SERIOUSLY
THE GREATEST THING
THAT'S EVER HAPPENED.

25:12.417 --> 25:14.291
-OH, MY GOD.
-IT'S TRUE.

25:14.291 --> 25:15.917
THAT'S, LIKE,
THE MOST AMAZING THING

25:15.917 --> 25:17.875
ANYONE HAS EVER SAID TO ME
IN MY ENTIRE LIFE.

25:17.875 --> 25:20.375
AND I DON'T EVEN THINK
JENNIFER LAWRENCE IS THAT HOT.

25:20.375 --> 25:24.125
♪ GIVE IT UP,
GIVE IT ALL THE WAY ♪

25:24.125 --> 25:26.667
♪ WE DON'T CARE
ABOUT YESTERDAY ♪

25:26.667 --> 25:30.875
♪ PLAYING WITH FIRE
TILL WE BURN OUT AND FADE AWAY ♪

25:30.875 --> 25:32.291
♪ WE'RE NEVER... ♪

25:32.291 --> 25:34.875
EMMA, YOU HAVEN'T SEEN LEO
LATELY, HAVE YOU?

25:34.875 --> 25:37.000
-I CAN'T FIND HIM
ANYWHERE.
-HE WAS IN MY ROOM
A WHILE AGO.

25:37.000 --> 25:38.667
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

25:38.667 --> 25:40.208
EVERYTHING'S FINE.

25:40.208 --> 25:43.750
PROBABLY.

25:43.750 --> 25:46.959
Sarah: WE ALREADY GOT A CRAPLOAD
OF FREE PRESSED JUICE.

25:46.959 --> 25:48.625
WHAT I'M LOOKING FOR
IS SOME TRANSPO.

25:48.625 --> 25:50.375
THANKS AGAIN, LINDS.
YOU'RE THE BEST.

25:50.375 --> 25:51.750
LOVE YOU.
KISS, KISS.

25:51.750 --> 25:54.291
YOU MUST BE KARA'S MOMS.
I'M EMMA.

25:54.291 --> 25:55.792
OH, I'M SARAH.
THIS IS DANIELLA.

25:55.792 --> 25:57.250
NICE TO MEET YOU.
ARE YOU FRIENDS WITH KARA?

25:57.250 --> 25:58.834
"FRIENDS" IS A STRONG WORD.

25:58.834 --> 26:00.875
I'D SAY WE'RE MORE
LIKE ACQUAINTANCES --

26:00.875 --> 26:03.208
SIMILAR IN AGE, FEMALE.

26:03.208 --> 26:06.291
-AREN'T YOU ADORABLE?
LOVE THAT DAINTY CHAPEAU.
-THANK YOU.

26:06.291 --> 26:11.125
DO YOU GUYS HAVE A MINUTE
TO TALK ABOUT KARA?

26:11.125 --> 26:12.375
IS SHE BULLYING YOU?

26:12.375 --> 26:14.709
ACTUALLY, YES, BUT THAT'S
NOT WHAT I'M WORRIED ABOUT.

26:14.709 --> 26:16.709
SHE'S GOING THROUGH A LOT
RIGHT NOW

26:16.709 --> 26:18.166
AND COULD REALLY USE
YOUR SUPPORT.

26:18.166 --> 26:20.125
UH, YEAH,
THAT'S WHY WE'RE HERE.

26:20.125 --> 26:22.750
HAVE YOU HEARD ABOUT OUR
CAMPAIGN TO RAISE AWARENESS
FOR KARA'S CONDITION?

26:22.750 --> 26:24.125
#HeartAndSoul.

26:24.125 --> 26:26.166
IT WAS SARAH'S IDEA.
SHE'S A MARKETING GENIUS.

26:26.166 --> 26:28.583
I'M ACTUALLY TALKING ABOUT
A DIFFERENT KIND OF SUPPORT.

26:28.583 --> 26:31.000
NOT THAT YOUR CAMPAIGN
ISN'T GREAT, IT'S JUST...

26:31.000 --> 26:35.583
WHAT I THINK KARA NEEDS RIGHT
NOW IS SOMEONE TO LISTEN TO HER.

26:35.583 --> 26:37.458
YOU KNOW,
AS THEODORE ROOSEVELT SAID,

26:37.458 --> 26:40.125
"NO ONE CARES HOW MUCH
YOU KNOW UNTIL THEY KNOW
HOW MUCH YOU CARE."

26:40.125 --> 26:42.000
<i>SHE IS ONE SMART COOKIE.</i>

26:42.000 --> 26:44.750
<i>TOO BAD</i>
<i>SHE WON'T EAT A COOKIE.</i>

26:44.750 --> 26:46.709
SHE NEEDS HER PARENTS.

26:46.959 --> 26:47.917
YOU'RE RIGHT.

26:47.917 --> 26:48.875
YOU'RE ABSOLUTELY RIGHT.

26:48.875 --> 26:51.792
THANK YOU SO MUCH FOR TALKING
TO US ABOUT THAT, EMMA.

26:51.792 --> 26:53.750
ANYTIME.

26:57.750 --> 27:00.166
WE SHOULD GET HER
TO TWEET.

27:02.917 --> 27:04.667
WHERE THE HELL IS
EVERYBODY?

27:04.667 --> 27:06.458
I'M WAITING ON UPDATES
ON THE KID.

27:06.458 --> 27:08.417
<i>OH, BY THE WAY, THAT'S RUBEN.</i>

27:08.417 --> 27:10.583
<i>HE'S A HIPPIE HYPOCHONDRIAC</i>
<i>WHO LIVES HERE AT THE HOSPITAL.</i>

27:10.583 --> 27:12.166
<i>SAY THAT THREE TIMES FAST.</i>

27:12.166 --> 27:15.542
THE KID IS OUT OF SURGERY,
AND LEO'S OUT OF THE BUILDING.

27:15.542 --> 27:17.208
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

27:17.208 --> 27:19.458
HE TOOK HIS SHOES --
BOTH OF THEM --

27:19.458 --> 27:21.625
AND HE WORE HIS LEG.

27:21.625 --> 27:23.208
WELL, I'LL BE DAMNED.

27:23.208 --> 27:24.709
GOOD FOR HIM.

27:24.709 --> 27:26.625
-KENJI!
-AAH!

27:26.625 --> 27:28.667
YOU RANG?

27:28.667 --> 27:30.125
WE NEED TO FIND
LEO ROTH<i> NOW.</i>

27:30.125 --> 27:32.000
I THINK YOU BURST
MY EARDRUM.

27:32.000 --> 27:34.834
THIS IS COLLETTE.
GUYS, THIS IS LEO.

27:34.834 --> 27:37.041
Leo:
HI. I'M -- I'M LEO.

27:37.041 --> 27:39.333
THIS IS SANDRA AND KYLE.

27:39.333 --> 27:42.542
LEO, MAN, IT'S TIME TO FLEECE
THIS FUNCTION.

27:42.542 --> 27:44.750
[ LAUGHS ]
I CAN'T BELIVE HE SAID THAT.

27:44.750 --> 27:46.041
THIS GUY'S SO FUNNY.

27:46.041 --> 27:47.208
I LOVE HIM.
HE'S LIKE MY BROTHER.

27:47.208 --> 27:48.542
BRO,
IS THAT LEG HURTING?

27:48.542 --> 27:50.250
NO, I'M FINE.

27:50.250 --> 27:53.875
LOOK, MAN, EMMA JUST TEXTED ME
ASKING WHERE YOU WERE,

27:53.875 --> 27:56.667
-AND JACKSON IS ON THE HUNT,
SO --
-OKAY, SO GO HOME.

27:56.667 --> 27:59.041
I'M NOT GONNA LEAVE
YOU. YOU CAN'T EVEN
WALK BACK BY YOURSELF.

27:59.041 --> 28:00.667
WHY ARE YOU BEING
SUCH A DICK?

28:00.667 --> 28:02.583
HEY, LEO,
CHILL OUT, MAN.

28:02.583 --> 28:04.166
NO, YOU NEED TO CHILL OUT.
I DON'T WANT YOU HERE.

28:04.166 --> 28:06.750
I DON'T NEED YOU HERE.
I'M ALL GOOD.

28:06.750 --> 28:08.166
I THINK
HE WANTS YOU TO GO.

28:08.166 --> 28:11.667
♪ DON'T MESS WITH ME ♪

28:11.667 --> 28:13.792
YEAH, I GOT THAT.

28:13.792 --> 28:16.542
SEE YOU LATER,<i> BROTHER.</i>

28:16.542 --> 28:19.750
[ UP-TEMPO POP MUSIC PLAYING ]

28:22.208 --> 28:28.208
[ GROANS SOFTLY ]

28:28.208 --> 28:31.291
Sarah: KARA,
WE WANT TO TALK TO YOU.

28:31.291 --> 28:33.375
MM. MNH-MNH.

28:33.375 --> 28:35.291
WE WANTED TO APOLOGIZE.

28:35.291 --> 28:38.125
UM, OKAY.

28:38.125 --> 28:39.959
WE'VE BEEN
REALLY NEGLECTFUL.

28:39.959 --> 28:41.709
WE'VE BEEN SO CONSUMED
WITH YOUR CAMPAIGN

28:41.709 --> 28:44.625
THAT WE HAVEN'T EVEN FOCUSED ON
THE PERSON WHO MATTERS MOST.

28:44.625 --> 28:45.917
THIS EVENT
IS IN YOUR HONOR,

28:45.917 --> 28:48.208
AND WE HAVEN'T EVEN INCLUDED
ANY OF YOUR HOSPITAL FRIENDS.

28:48.208 --> 28:51.041
I DON'T HAVE
ANY FRIENDS HERE.

28:51.041 --> 28:53.709
WELL, WHAT ABOUT EMMA? WE WERE
JUST TALKING WITH HER ABOUT YOU.

28:53.709 --> 28:54.542
[ SCOFFS ]

28:54.542 --> 28:57.041
YOU WERE TALKING TO EMMA
ABOUT ME BEHIND MY BACK?

28:57.041 --> 28:59.375
-WELL, NOT BEHIND YOUR BACK.
YOU'RE MISUNDERSTANDING.
-OKAY, STOP IT, KARA.

28:59.375 --> 29:01.208
I MEAN,
DON'T LET YOUR JEALOUSY RUIN

29:01.208 --> 29:04.333
WHAT COULD ULTIMATELY BE
A VERY BENEFICIAL RELATIONSHIP.

29:04.333 --> 29:07.500
IF ANYTHING, YOU SHOULD STRIVE
TO BE A BIT MORE LIKE EMMA.

29:07.500 --> 29:10.166
SHE'S POISED, SMART,
SHE PULLS OFF THOSE CHIC HATS.

29:10.166 --> 29:11.750
SHE COULD BE EXACTLY
WHAT YOU NEED

29:11.750 --> 29:13.917
TO APPEAL
TO THAT STUPID TRANSPLANT BOARD.

29:13.917 --> 29:15.834
YOU HAVE GOT
TO BE KIDDING ME.

29:18.083 --> 29:21.834
48 HOURS INTO LABOR, I KNEW
THAT KID WAS GONNA BE A PROBLEM.

29:26.959 --> 29:29.750
<i>THE ONLY THING HARDER THAN</i>
<i>BREAKING OUT OF A HOSPITAL --</i>

29:29.750 --> 29:30.917
<i>BREAKING BACK IN.</i>

29:40.709 --> 29:43.333
HELLO, DASH.
HEY, BRITTANY.

29:43.333 --> 29:45.333
MM, DON'T EVEN TRY
TO SWEET-TALK ME.

29:45.333 --> 29:46.917
NURSE JACKSON IS LOOKING
FOR LEO,

29:46.917 --> 29:48.458
AND I KNOW
YOU KNOW WHERE HE IS.

29:48.458 --> 29:50.083
I DO.

29:50.083 --> 29:51.667
OH.

29:51.667 --> 29:53.083
SO LET'S GO TELL
NURSE JACKSON.

29:55.125 --> 29:56.041
I HAVE A BETTER IDEA.

30:01.291 --> 30:03.709
YOU BONY BITCH.

30:03.709 --> 30:05.458
NICE TO SEE YOU, TOO.

30:05.458 --> 30:08.125
YOU KNOW, I EXPECT MY CHEER
SQUAD TO STAB ME IN THE BACK,

30:08.125 --> 30:10.417
BECAUSE, HONESTLY, THEY WERE
MOSTLY RAISED BY WOLVES,

30:10.417 --> 30:12.834
BUT I DIDN'T EXPECT THIS CRAP
FROM YOU.

30:12.834 --> 30:15.333
ONCE AGAIN, I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

30:15.333 --> 30:18.792
I'M TALKING ABOUT MY MOM
AND HER LATEST OBSESSION.

30:18.792 --> 30:22.000
-YOU?
-NO, YOU.

30:22.000 --> 30:24.291
SHE THINKS
YOU'RE ADORABLE AND PERFECT,

30:24.291 --> 30:27.083
AND SHE SAID I SHOULD STRIVE
TO BE MORE LIKE YOU.

30:27.083 --> 30:29.417
SHE ACTUALLY USED
THE WORD "STRIVE,"

30:29.417 --> 30:31.125
WHICH MAKES ME WANT TO GAG.

30:31.125 --> 30:34.375
HEY, I WANT TO GAG.
LOOK, I'M MORE LIKE YOU ALREADY.

30:34.375 --> 30:35.792
YEAH, WELL,
I'M NOT BULIMIC.

30:35.792 --> 30:36.875
OH, SAME DIFFERENCE.

30:36.875 --> 30:39.333
MOST GIRLS I KNOW WOULD KILL
TO HAVE AN EATING DISORDER.

30:39.333 --> 30:42.083
AND MOST GIRLS I KNOW
WOULD KILL YOU.

30:42.083 --> 30:43.834
[ SCOFFS ]

30:55.333 --> 30:57.709
LOOK, I'M SORRY,
ALL RIGHT?

30:57.709 --> 30:59.834
I WAS GENUINELY JUST TRYING TO
GET YOUR MOM TO LISTEN TO YOU.

30:59.834 --> 31:03.500
-WELL, SHE'S NEVER
GOING TO CHANGE.
-MAYBE NOT.

31:03.500 --> 31:06.041
BUT THERE'S STILL HOPE
FOR YOU.

31:06.041 --> 31:09.250
THIS MORNING,
YOU OPENED UP A LITTLE BIT,

31:09.250 --> 31:12.041
AND, HONESTLY, IT MADE ME
SEE YOU A LITTLE DIFFERENTLY.

31:12.041 --> 31:14.250
LIKE A LOT PRETTIER?

31:14.250 --> 31:16.000
INSIDE.

31:16.000 --> 31:17.583
I USED TO THINK
YOUR SOUL WAS BLACK,

31:17.583 --> 31:19.208
BUT NOW IT'S MORE
OF A CHARCOAL GRAY.

31:19.208 --> 31:20.917
MY POINT IS,

31:20.917 --> 31:23.000
YOU CAN CHANGE YOUR RELATIONSHIP
WITH YOUR MOM, TOO.

31:23.000 --> 31:24.083
YEAH, RIGHT.

31:24.083 --> 31:26.208
MAYBE TRY BEING HONEST
ABOUT HOW YOU FEEL.

31:26.208 --> 31:29.208
YOU KNOW, TELL DANIELLA ONE TRUE
THING AND SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

31:29.208 --> 31:32.959
DANIELLA IS NOT MY MOM.

31:32.959 --> 31:36.750
SHE'S MY FORMER NANNY
TURNED STEP-MONSTER.

31:36.750 --> 31:39.375
REALLY? THAT'S SO WEIRD.
I THOUGHT THAT --

31:39.375 --> 31:40.583
WHAT?

31:40.583 --> 31:44.458
NEVER MIND.

31:42.125 --> 31:44.458
SAY IT.

31:49.458 --> 31:52.333
[ UP-TEMPO POP MUSIC PLAYING,
INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

31:52.333 --> 31:54.041
DO YOU HAVE A CONDOM?

31:54.041 --> 31:56.875
OH, UM [GROANS]

31:56.875 --> 31:59.041
THAT'S OKAY.
I HAVE SOME.

32:01.875 --> 32:03.291
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:03.291 --> 32:06.166
[ INDISTINCT SINGING ]

32:14.583 --> 32:17.208
-DO YOU LIKE THAT?
-[ CHUCKLES ] YEAH.

32:20.291 --> 32:22.583
WAIT. DON'T.
WHAT'S WRONG?

32:22.583 --> 32:24.917
I SAID STOP.

32:24.917 --> 32:26.542
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

32:26.542 --> 32:29.083
I DON'T HAVE A PROBLEM. YOU'RE
THE ONE ACTING LIKE A SLUT.

32:32.625 --> 32:34.417
UM, I'M SORRY.

32:35.583 --> 32:38.125
WAIT, E-ELISE.
WAIT, ELISE.

32:38.125 --> 32:39.208
[ GRUNTS ]

32:45.291 --> 32:48.125
GOT YOUR TEXT.
YOU OKAY?

32:48.125 --> 32:50.542
YOU KNOW WHERE LEO IS?
LEO?

32:50.542 --> 32:52.417
LEO SAID HE'D COME TO SEE ME
AFTER MY SURGERY,

32:52.417 --> 32:54.792
BUT HE HASN'T BEEN HERE
ALL DAY.

32:54.792 --> 32:57.625
HE KNOWS ABOUT MY LEG,
DOESN'T HE?

32:57.625 --> 32:59.792
YEAH. YEAH, HE DOES.

32:59.792 --> 33:02.291
PROBABLY HATES ME, RIGHT?

33:02.291 --> 33:05.875
I DON'T BLAME HIM.
I'D HATE ME, TOO.

33:05.875 --> 33:08.458
ALL RIGHT,
LOOK, UH, JORDI...

33:08.458 --> 33:12.458
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT
WHAT WE SAW DURING YOUR SURGERY.

33:12.458 --> 33:14.083
THOUGHT IT WENT WELL.

33:14.083 --> 33:15.917
THOUGHT THAT'S WHY
I GOT TO KEEP MY LEG.

33:18.792 --> 33:20.417
YOU GOT TO KEEP YOUR LEG

33:20.417 --> 33:23.583
BECAUSE THERE WAS NO REASON
FOR ME TO TAKE YOUR LEG OFF.

33:23.583 --> 33:26.583
THE, UH -- THE CANCER HAS SPREAD
TO YOUR SOFT TISSUE.

33:29.709 --> 33:32.834
OH.

33:32.834 --> 33:35.500
MAYBE EVEN STARTED THERE
AND MOVED INTO YOUR BONE MARROW.

33:35.500 --> 33:37.208
AT THIS POINT, YOU KNOW,

33:37.208 --> 33:39.625
IT'S EASY TO MISDIAGNOSE
SOFT TISSUE FOR OSTEOSARCOMA,

33:39.625 --> 33:41.166
BUT REMOVING YOUR LEG
WOULD NOT HAVE HELPED.

33:41.166 --> 33:43.375
SO WHAT HAPPENS NOW?

33:43.375 --> 33:45.333
WE'RE GONNA START YOU
ON SOME CHEMOTHERAPY,

33:45.333 --> 33:47.041
WE'RE GONNA TRY
AND SHRINK THE TUMORS,

33:47.041 --> 33:49.291
AND WE'RE GONNA SEE
HOW YOU AND YOUR CANCER RESPOND

33:49.291 --> 33:51.333
TO THE TREATMENT
BEFORE WE TRY ANOTHER SURGERY.

33:51.333 --> 33:54.917
SO THERE'LL BE
ANOTHER SURGERY?
YEAH.

33:54.917 --> 33:57.166
WHICH MEANS THAT WE WILL NEED
SOMEONE FROM YOUR FAMILY

33:57.166 --> 33:58.667
TO SIGN OFF
ON THE TREATMENT.

33:58.667 --> 34:00.625
-YOUR GRANDMOTHER --
-SHE WON'T SIGN OFF.

34:00.625 --> 34:02.333
SHE DOESN'T BELIEVE
I HAVE CANCER.

34:02.333 --> 34:03.875
MAYBE IF I CALL.

34:03.875 --> 34:05.750
IT DOESN'T MATTER.
SHE HATES DOCTORS.

34:05.750 --> 34:08.667
LET'S TALK ABOUT THIS LATER,
OKAY?

34:08.667 --> 34:11.667
UM, RIGHT NOW,
IS THERE, UH...

34:11.667 --> 34:14.417
I-IS THERE ANYBODY
THAT YOU WANT ME TO CALL?

34:14.417 --> 34:16.917
IS THERE ANYBODY
THAT YOU WANT HERE WITH YOU?

34:16.917 --> 34:19.792
♪ COME SO FAR ♪

34:19.792 --> 34:23.083
I TOLD YOU...
I GOT NO ONE.

34:23.083 --> 34:29.583
♪ SO LET ME KNOW
WHEN WE GET THERE ♪

34:29.583 --> 34:32.375
♪ IF WE GET THERE ♪

34:32.375 --> 34:36.041
<i>SOMETIMES, THE LONGEST MILE</i>
<i>IS THE ONE YOU WALK ALONE.</i>

34:37.375 --> 34:40.959
[ RAP MUSIC PLAYING ]

34:40.959 --> 34:45.083
UH, COULD SOMEONE PLEASE TELL ME
WHERE I MIGHT FIND LEO ROTH?

34:45.083 --> 34:47.375
ALL RIGHT,
WHO ORDERED A STRIPPER?

34:47.375 --> 34:48.917
-[ CHEERS ]
-EXCUSE ME?

34:48.917 --> 34:50.917
HOT NURSE.
IT'S A COMMON STRIPPER THEME.

34:50.917 --> 34:52.709
-I'D GO WITH IT.
-OH, OKAY.

34:52.709 --> 34:54.333
WELL, FOR THE RECORD,

34:54.333 --> 34:56.583
I'M NOT SURE WHY
ANY OF YOU WOULD COME HERE

34:56.583 --> 34:58.625
AND RISK ALCOHOL POISONING,

34:58.625 --> 35:00.625
WHICH COULD LEAD
TO HEART PALPITATIONS

35:00.625 --> 35:02.417
AND DECREASED URINE OUTPUT.

35:02.417 --> 35:05.458
HEY, HOW -- HOW MUCH
FOR A PRIVATE LAP DANCE?

35:05.458 --> 35:06.583
[ CHEERING ]

35:06.583 --> 35:08.000
I AM NOT A STRIPPER.

35:08.000 --> 35:10.083
[ LAUGHTER ]

35:10.083 --> 35:11.583
Man: OW, OW!

35:14.667 --> 35:15.917
[ DOOR OPENS ]

35:15.917 --> 35:17.917
LEO.

35:21.417 --> 35:23.250
GET HIS LEFT SIDE.

35:25.250 --> 35:26.417
NOW, DASH.

35:28.625 --> 35:30.542
LEAN ON ME, LEO.
[ GRUNTS ] I GOT YOU.

35:30.542 --> 35:31.792
OKAY.

35:31.792 --> 35:33.959
-[ GRUNTS ]
-OKAY.

35:33.959 --> 35:36.625
OKAY, WAIT, WAIT.

35:50.583 --> 35:52.458
HE'S NOT ON THE ROOF.

35:52.458 --> 35:54.959
ALL RIGHT, I'M CALLING IT.
PEOPLE, WE'RE CODE PURPLE.

35:59.792 --> 36:01.834
HE WAS AT THE COFFEE SHOP
DOWN THE STREET.

36:01.834 --> 36:04.000
I TRIED TO TELL HIM THAT
CAFFEINE WOULD STUNT HIS GROWTH,

36:04.000 --> 36:06.291
BUT...YOU KNOW KIDS.

36:06.291 --> 36:09.166
-THEY JUST DON'T LISTEN.
-BRITTANY.

36:13.166 --> 36:15.458
NICE JOB.

36:23.625 --> 36:25.834
WHERE'S MOM?

36:25.834 --> 36:29.500
WELL, SHE'S DEFINITELY NOT
OUTSIDE SMOKING A CIGARETTE,

36:29.500 --> 36:32.166
BECAUSE SHE KNOWS
HOW MUCH I HATE THAT.

36:37.000 --> 36:38.583
CUTE KID.

36:38.583 --> 36:40.667
<i>OR DEVASTATINGLY HANDSOME.</i>

36:40.667 --> 36:43.875
-HE REMINDS ME
OF THE FIRST BOY I NANNIED FOR.
-SUTTON.

36:43.875 --> 36:46.667
YOU REMEMBER SUTTON?

36:46.667 --> 36:50.417
-YOU ONLY TALKED ABOUT HIM
THE FIRST SIX YEARS OF MY LIFE.

36:50.417 --> 36:52.875
HE WAS A SWEET KID.

36:52.875 --> 36:54.208
HIS PARENTS
WERE GOING THROUGH

36:54.208 --> 36:56.000
THIS HORRIBLE DIVORCE
WHEN I STARTED.

36:56.000 --> 36:57.709
I REMEMBER FEELING SO BADLY
FOR HIM.

36:57.709 --> 37:00.834
YOU DIDN'T FEEL
QUITE AS BAD

37:00.834 --> 37:03.333
WHEN YOU CAUSED
<i>MY </i>PARENTS' DIVORCE.

37:03.333 --> 37:06.291
I DIDN'T CAUSE
THEIR DIVORCE.

37:06.291 --> 37:07.875
WHATEVER.

37:10.041 --> 37:12.166
I KNOW.

37:15.917 --> 37:18.709
SO, IF MOM'S OUTSIDE,
SMOKING A CIGARETTE,

37:18.709 --> 37:21.291
SHE MUST BE STRESSED.

37:21.291 --> 37:24.041
SHE'S NOT GONNA BE ABLE
TO GET ME A NEW HEART, IS SHE?

37:26.041 --> 37:28.041
I DON'T KNOW.

37:32.667 --> 37:35.208
SO WHAT NOW?

37:35.208 --> 37:38.875
WELL, I'M NOT SURE.

37:38.875 --> 37:41.625
BUT I DO KNOW ONE THING.

37:41.625 --> 37:44.709
YOU'RE BRAVER
THAN YOU BELIEVE,

37:44.709 --> 37:47.208
STRONGER THAN YOU SEEM,
AND...

37:47.208 --> 37:50.083
Both:
SMARTER THAN YOU THINK.

37:50.083 --> 37:52.125
DON'T BE WINNIE THE POOH-ING
MY ASS.

37:52.125 --> 37:54.000
I'M NOT FIVE YEARS OLD
ANYMORE.

37:54.000 --> 37:56.208
THAT IS TRUE.

37:56.208 --> 37:58.417
BUT YOU'LL ALWAYS BE
MY KARA BEAR.

38:00.750 --> 38:02.750
Sarah:
GOOD. YOU'RE BACK.

38:02.750 --> 38:05.083
UH, ELLEN'S ASSISTANT
CAN TALK, BUT SHE'S ON
A FLIGHT AT 9:00 --

38:05.083 --> 38:07.291
MOM, I HAVE TO TELL YOU
SOMETHING.

38:07.291 --> 38:09.083
MM-HMM.

38:09.083 --> 38:10.750
IT'S NOT AN EASY THING
FOR ME TO ADMIT,

38:10.750 --> 38:14.125
BUT I FEEL LIKE
I NEED TO BE HONEST WITH YOU.

38:14.125 --> 38:15.542
WHAT IS IT?

38:18.709 --> 38:21.208
I'VE NEVER SEEN "ELLEN."

38:21.208 --> 38:23.250
WHAT?

38:23.250 --> 38:25.208
HOW IS THAT POSSIBLE?

38:25.208 --> 38:27.208
THE WOMAN IS SYNDICATED,
FOR GOD'S SAKE.

38:27.208 --> 38:29.208
AND I'M SURE SHE'S FABULOUS,

38:29.208 --> 38:30.959
DESPITE HER UNFORTUNATE
HAIR CHOICES,

38:30.959 --> 38:34.375
BUT I FEEL LIKE A HYPOCRITE
ASKING HER TO HELP ME.

38:34.375 --> 38:38.208
I THINK IT WOULD BE BETTER
IF I JUST FIGURE IT OUT MYSELF.

38:38.208 --> 38:42.250
WELL, IF THAT'S WHAT YOU WANT,
THEN WE'RE HERE FOR YOU.

38:42.250 --> 38:44.250
ABSOLUTELY, WE ARE.

38:44.250 --> 38:47.709
I MEAN, AGREE TO DISAGREE,
BUT IT'S YOUR DECISION.

38:47.709 --> 38:50.291
[ PHOSPHORESCENT'S
"SONG FOR ZULA" PLAYS ]

38:53.000 --> 38:57.583
♪ SOME SAY LOVE
IS A BURNING THING... ♪

38:57.583 --> 39:00.834
Kara: FOR THE RECORD,
I'M FAMILIAR WITH PORTIA'S WORK.

39:00.834 --> 39:04.166
[ SIGHS ]

39:04.166 --> 39:09.166
♪ ...OH, BUT I KNOW LOVE
AS A FADING THING... ♪

39:09.166 --> 39:11.667
Bartender:
ROUGH DAY, DOC?

39:11.667 --> 39:13.250
YEAH.

39:13.250 --> 39:15.000
SOME DAYS ARE HARDER
THAN OTHERS.

39:15.000 --> 39:18.542
-I DON'T KNOW HOW YOU DO IT.
-♪ HONEY, I SAW LOVE ♪

39:18.542 --> 39:21.291
♪ YOU SEE, IT CAME TO ME ♪

39:21.291 --> 39:26.583
♪ IT PUT ITS FACE UP TO MY FACE
SO I COULD SEE ♪

39:26.583 --> 39:32.625
♪ YEAH, THEN I SAW LOVE
DISFIGURE ME ♪

39:32.625 --> 39:38.166
♪ INTO SOMETHING
I AM NOT RECOGNIZING ♪

39:43.917 --> 39:46.625
YOU KNOW,
YOU WOULDN'T BE IN SO MUCH PAIN

39:46.625 --> 39:48.834
IF YOU WENT
TO PHYSICAL THERAPY.

39:48.834 --> 39:50.250
COULD'VE WALKED HOME.

39:50.250 --> 39:52.000
I'VE BEEN AFRAID
THAT IF WORE THE LEG,

39:52.000 --> 39:53.709
IT WOULD BE LIKE
THIS REALLY HAPPENED.

39:53.709 --> 39:56.375
BUT IT<i> DID </i>HAPPEN.
IT HAPPENED TO YOU.

40:00.417 --> 40:03.375
I THOUGHT,
WITH JORDI'S SURGERY,

40:03.375 --> 40:05.875
THAT THERE WOULD BE
ANOTHER PERSON HERE LIKE ME.

40:05.875 --> 40:08.083
[ SIGHS ]

40:08.083 --> 40:11.083
THIS MORNING, WHEN I WAS WAITING
FOR HIM TO COME OUT...

40:11.083 --> 40:14.208
I WANTED TO BE THERE
FOR HIM.

40:16.542 --> 40:21.625
BUT, REALLY, I WAS COUNTING
ON HIM BEING THERE FOR ME.

40:21.625 --> 40:26.917
SO I WOULDN'T FEEL
SO...ALONE.

40:26.917 --> 40:30.083
YOU'RE NOT ALONE, LEO.

40:30.083 --> 40:32.000
WE'RE ALL HERE FOR YOU.

40:32.000 --> 40:33.542
I KNOW.

40:35.875 --> 40:38.250
BUT SOMETIMES,
I CAN'T FEEL IT.

40:38.250 --> 40:40.083
I CAN'T TAKE IT IN,
YOU KNOW?

40:43.166 --> 40:46.250
YOU CAN'T RUN AWAY
FROM YOUR LIFE.

40:46.250 --> 40:50.000
IT'S YOURS
AND IT'S PRECIOUS.

40:50.000 --> 40:52.250
YOU JUST HAVE TO CLAIM IT.

40:54.375 --> 40:57.166
I THINK THAT'S THE NICEST THING
YOU'VE EVER SAID TO ME.

40:57.166 --> 41:01.291
[ CHUCKLES ] WELL,
THAT'S WHAT REAL MONKEY LOVE IS.

41:02.834 --> 41:04.625
DID THAT SOUND WEIRD
BECAUSE I'M STILL DRUNK

41:04.625 --> 41:08.125
OR JUST BECAUSE IT'S WEIRD?

41:08.125 --> 41:10.458
BOTH.

41:10.458 --> 41:14.166
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:14.166 --> 41:19.583
♪ I'VE BEEN SELLING MY NAME
FOR THE SAKE OF WHO KNOWS ♪

41:21.291 --> 41:27.208
♪ I'VE BEEN TRYING TO EXPLAIN
HOW IT'S ALL GONNA GO ♪

41:27.208 --> 41:33.208
♪ I DON'T TAKE MY LIFE
FOR GRANTED... ♪

41:33.208 --> 41:34.667
HEY.

41:34.667 --> 41:37.208
HEY. TOUGH DAY?

41:37.208 --> 41:39.250
♪ I'VE BEEN WAKING UP TIGHT ♪

41:39.250 --> 41:42.125
WASN'T GREAT.
OH, REALLY? GOD.

41:42.125 --> 41:44.000
-♪ DAY AFTER DAY ♪
-[ CHUCKLES ]

41:44.000 --> 41:46.083
♪ BUT I DON'T TAKE MY LIFE... ♪

41:46.083 --> 41:47.709
I KNOW
EXACTLY HOW YOU FEEL.

41:47.709 --> 41:50.333
♪ ...FOR GRANTED ♪

41:50.333 --> 41:54.750
♪ I'M GONNA HOLD ON TIGHT
TO WHAT I'VE BEEN HANDED ♪

41:54.750 --> 41:56.667
<i>SOMETIMES, YOU DON'T NEED</i>

41:56.667 --> 42:00.000
<i>TO WALK IN ANOTHER PERSON'S</i>
<i>SHOES TO KNOW HOW THEY FEEL.</i>

42:00.000 --> 42:04.291
<i>SOMETIMES, THE BEST THING</i>
<i>YOU CAN DO IS SIT BESIDE THEM.</i>

42:04.291 --> 42:11.625
♪ DON'T TAKE YOUR LI-I-I-FE
FOR GRANTED ♪

42:11.625 --> 42:21.625
♪ 'CAUSE YOU JUST DON'T KNOW
HOW LONG YOU WILL HAVE IT ♪
